column5: I have a wish list for Santa, I hope he checks it twice.  Snowmobile boots, a new computer chair (an OFC necessity for long hours of reading), warm gloves, a waterproof windproof fishing jacket, and a computer tablet and stylus to use with Photoshop.  What's on YOUR list?  Pam
My tripod for the camera and the new camera I want to go along with it will make my xmas good
Hmmm....I'd like a GPS/Sonar combo for the boat for next year!!!  (Bly...you reading this?)
If Santa brought me a nice Shimano baitcasting setup, and some fishing tools I'd be mighty happy with him
More free time to go fishing
Peace on earth, goodwill to man, and a baitcaster setup.  JF
Iron Maiden   Ticket
Wouldn't mind a Shimano Curado 201DHSV. Not sure that I've been that good though......
I hope santa is reading this because I have just found out from the marina that I blew 2 pistons in my 150 v-max so I hope that santa can bring me the 150 evinrude e-tec iv always wanted.
4 inches of good hard ice.  C'mon Santa it doesn't cost a thing... Talk to your buddy Jack Frost... Work with us here will ya.   Hookset.
Navionics Hotmaps for Canada 2007.   (Already got it) New fishing net (to be picked up soon).  Battin' 1,000 so far.
the day off?  With pay???  I know, I don't ask for much  Maureen
Santa to spread Joy to all... Ken

Health and happiness for my family and friends is tops on my list. I honestly can't think of any material things that I want or need. A few Rapala Countdowns would be nice. Size 5 or 7. Any color will do.
Rich the navionics is on my list as well!!! I am secretly looking at a Mathews Switchback that the wife doesnt know about!
super 7 jackpot Friday and the 6/49 Saturday, then heck its all good from there.

Cmon Dan !!!!... while I gotta agree wholeheartedly on the Health and Happiness .... but seriously man .... You of alllll people need to be wishin for a chance to swap spit with a 10lb + speck ... at least once before her release ... and of course I'd be happy just to be the cameraman   oh ... and sorry Mods .... I gotta do it ... after all its just a wish  (delete if you must) but here is my wish (assuming first I got all of the above) ...
Tch, Tch, Tch - your in BIG trouble now mister!  -  and thanks   Don

LOL CJ. If Santa could bring a spit swapping session with a 10 lb. Brookie, it would be tops on my list. As for your avatar, well, I have to be good here. Nice to hear from you Bud. You're not smoking yet, are you??
Nope ... 269 days and counting
Excellent!!!   :thumbsup_anim:
A transfer to Waterloo Region Canon Rebel Ti 14ft aluminum deep and wide Dodge Ram 4x4 or Chev Silverado
